	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Do you want to help build one? It'd basically need a hardware version of the NSF mapper, and I think we'd need ~2MB of ROM. I'd be willing to code a menu and whatnot to show some graphics, but the idea of building the mapper hardware is daunting to me.</div><br /><br />I'd love to.<br /><br />I'm not really sure how the whole NSF mapper/player thing is setup though...  Is <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Talk:NSF" class="postlink">this</a> the best documentation we have on it?<br /><br />Loopy's <a href="http://home.comcast.net/~olimar/NES/" class="postlink">source</a> has some mention of counters and such.<br /><br />I'm having a hard time wrapping my head around how this whole thing works.  It's sounding like it all depends on the nsf player you create that will play .nsf files.  From what I gather there is no specific 'nsf mapper'.  To some degree we'd be creating a nsf player that was most easily played on low cost hardware.<br /><br />Perhaps branching off to another topic is in order.  I'd be interested, and I think should be possible with some of the stuff I have right now.  Just need to better understand the 'mapper' and what options we do and don't have without making a ton of work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
