		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: 2A03 Puritans compilation album</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello. I am one of the composers from the soundtrack.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> <br /><br />With a couple of exceptions, the majority of the tracks were made in Famitracker. The exceptions are TQ-Jam's (which is done with MML) and my song, which was made with Schism Tracker and then converted to .nsf file via mukunda's it2nsf.<br /><br />The documentation for it2nsf states that the memory mapping to $E000-FFFF must not be changed outside of its music routine. That's the DPCM data access. $A000-CFFF is not used in it2nsf.<br /><br />I don't know what the other ones use for memory mapping, but as long as you don't accidentally switch the banks used for DPCM (I'd think that would be the only place not to touch the bank switches), I think you should be good.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
